### Creating a company
- Click **Add**. The **Create Company **form is displayed.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Enter the following details (mandatory fields are marked with an asterisk *):

**Section**

**Field**

**Mandatory**

**Description**

**General Information**

**Company name**

X

Name of the company (a combination of alphanumeric characters, spaces, and special characters)

**Account**

X

Select the account to which the company belongs.

> Note

A company may only be associated with an account. An account may have one or more companies.

**Profiles**

Select the profile(s) to associate with the company.

> Note

Profiles are used to autofill company data when creating invoices.

Company profiles are defined and managed by Doxee Platform administrators.

> Important

This field is mandatory if you require to create invoices using the Doxee Platform **I nvoices **service.

**Tags**

**Tags**

Enter one or more tags (up to 10 tags, separated by a comma) to label the company. Tags may have a maximum length of 20 characters.

- Click **Save **to confirm.

> Note

For more information on how to create an account, see: [Doxee Platform Settings - Accounts](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-settings-accounts).

### Viewing the details of a company
Click on the name of a company to view its details.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

> Note

For more information on how to edit a company, see [Editing a company](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-settings-companies#editing-a-company) below.

> Note

The **History **panel lists all changes performed on the company, including the status icon, date and time, and name of the user who performed the action.

### Editing a company
- Click on the name of a company to view its details.

or:

Select the company that you want to modify and click **Edit**.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

- Edit the required information.

> Note

For more information on the available fields, see [Creating a company](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-settings-companies#creating-a-company) above.

- Click **Update **to confirm.

> Tip

If you make any changes to the company details and then click on a different tab or the **Back **browser button, the system displays the following prompt, allowing you to save, discard, or cancel the changes.
